<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>${project_name} Distribution Notes</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #0b1020;
      --bg-alt: #11182e;
      --panel: rgba(10, 16, 32, 0.86);
      --line: rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.22);
      --text: #e5edf7;
      --muted: #9db0ca;
      --accent: #4ade80;
      --accent-2: #38bdf8;
      --accent-3: #f59e0b;
      --shadow: 0 24px 60px rgba(2, 6, 23, 0.45);
    }

    * {
      box-sizing: border-box;
    }

    body {
      margin: 0;
      min-height: 100vh;
      font-family: "Segoe UI Variable Display", "Aptos", "Trebuchet MS", sans-serif;
      color: var(--text);
      background:
        radial-gradient(circle at top left, rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.18), transparent 28%),
        radial-gradient(circle at top right, rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.12), transparent 24%),
        linear-gradient(160deg, #060913 0%, #0b1020 48%, #121a30 100%);
    }

    main {
      width: min(960px, calc(100% - 32px));
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 40px 0 56px;
    }

    .hero,
    .section {
      background: var(--panel);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 24px;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow);
      backdrop-filter: blur(14px);
    }

    .hero {
      padding: 36px;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }

    .hero::after {
      content: "";
      position: absolute;
      inset: auto -120px -120px auto;
      width: 280px;
      height: 280px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.24), rgba(245, 158, 11, 0));
      pointer-events: none;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
      padding: 8px 14px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      background: rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.12);
      border: 1px solid rgba(56, 189, 248, 0.2);
      color: var(--accent-2);
      font-size: 0.82rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.12em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    h1 {
      margin: 18px 0 12px;
      font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
      line-height: 0.95;
    }

    .subtitle {
      max-width: 720px;
      margin: 0;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 1.06rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .buttons {
      display: flex;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      gap: 12px;
      margin-top: 28px;
    }

    .button {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      min-width: 160px;
      padding: 12px 18px;
      border-radius: 999px;
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
      transition: transform 140ms ease, box-shadow 140ms ease, border-color 140ms ease;
    }

    .button:hover {
      transform: translateY(-1px);
    }

    .button-primary {
      color: #07111f;
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--accent), #86efac);
      box-shadow: 0 12px 28px rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.18);
    }

    .button-secondary {
      color: var(--text);
      background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.7);
      border: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.24);
    }

    .grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
      gap: 16px;
      margin-top: 22px;
    }

    .card {
      padding: 18px 18px 16px;
      border-radius: 18px;
      background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.72);
      border: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.16);
    }

    .card strong {
      display: block;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      color: #f8fafc;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    .card p,
    li,
    .footer {
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .section {
      margin-top: 22px;
      padding: 28px 30px;
    }

    h2 {
      margin-top: 0;
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.04em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: var(--accent-3);
    }

    ul,
    ol {
      margin: 14px 0 0;
      padding-left: 22px;
    }

    a {
      color: var(--accent-2);
    }

    code {
      padding: 0.15rem 0.45rem;
      border-radius: 8px;
      background: rgba(15, 23, 42, 0.82);
      color: #dbeafe;
      font-family: "Cascadia Code", "Consolas", monospace;
    }

    .footer {
      margin-top: 18px;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    @media (max-width: 640px) {
      main {
        width: min(100% - 20px, 960px);
        padding-top: 18px;
      }

      .hero,
      .section {
        border-radius: 18px;
        padding: 24px 20px;
      }

      .button {
        width: 100%;
      }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <main>
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="eyebrow">${project_name_short} distribution notes</div>
      <h1>${project_name}</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">
        ${display_name} is a modernized Quake III Arena engine build that keeps retail compatibility, demo compatibility,
        speed, and cross-platform support as first-order constraints.
      </p>
      <div class="buttons">
        <a class="button button-primary" href="../README.md">Project README</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href="../BUILD.md">Build Guide</a>
        <a class="button button-secondary" href="../docs/TECHNICAL.md">Technical Notes</a>
      </div>
      <div class="grid">
        <article class="card">
          <strong>Base version</strong>
          <p>${version}</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <strong>Compatibility target</strong>
          <p>${compatibility_target}</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <strong>Stable tag format</strong>
          <p><code>${release_tag_example}</code></p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>What This Package Assumes</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>You already own the original Quake III Arena game data.</li>
        <li>The engine binary should live beside the retail data files or a configured base path.</li>
        <li>Retail assets should stay untouched; package only the engine-side additions here.</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Release Channels</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Stable releases use semantic tags such as <code>${release_tag_example}</code>.</li>
        <li>Nightly packages keep a moving <code>${nightly_tag}</code> release tag and include the build date plus commit in the archive filename.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Documentation</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="../README.md">README.md</a> keeps the user-facing overview concise.</li>
        <li><a href="../BUILD.md">BUILD.md</a> covers platform-specific compile steps.</li>
        <li><a href="../docs/TECHNICAL.md">docs/TECHNICAL.md</a> covers repository layout, versioning, and release flow.</li>
        <li><a href="../LICENSE">LICENSE</a> and <a href="../COPYING.txt">COPYING.txt</a> ship with the package.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="footer">Generated from the repository templates so distribution docs stay aligned with the tracked project version.</p>
    </section>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
